Mmm.

01:30.891 --> 01:32.758
    Okay, I'll check on you
        in a little bit.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.026
            (spits)

01:34.028 --> 01:35.694
   Like I want to get better.

01:35.696 --> 01:37.696
      Hey, wait a minute,
         who's missing?

01:37.698 --> 01:39.765
          Kuchi Kopi.
         Gah, the Kuch.

01:39.767 --> 01:42.067
   He's only my favorite toy
         in the world.

01:42.069 --> 01:44.436
      If I had a favorite.

01:44.438 --> 01:47.072
         Which I don't.

01:47.074 --> 01:48.607
        (clears throat)

01:48.609 --> 01:50.275
 (air horn blares, all scream)

01:50.277 --> 01:52.444
    Jeez, I thought we took
  the air horn away from her.

01:52.446 --> 01:54.613
              Did you hide it in
          your underwear drawer?
              Yes.

01:54.615 --> 01:55.881
               We know about the
               underwear drawer.

01:55.883 --> 01:57.449
       And about your underwear.

01:57.451 --> 01:59.785
   Not-so-tighty-not-so-whities.
       (air horn blares)

01:59.787 --> 02:01.553
Coming!

02:01.555 --> 02:02.754
       (air horn blares)
               Okay, okay, okay.

02:02.756 --> 02:04.723
Oh, good, you heard that.
             Yeah.

02:04.725 --> 02:07.593
  Listen, would you be a lamb
    and bring me Kuchi Kopi?

02:07.595 --> 02:10.062
    I would get him myself,
 but I'm just so sick and weak.

02:10.064 --> 02:12.397
          (fake cough)
       Sure, where is he?

02:12.399 --> 02:15.434
      In the bathroom next
         to the toilet.
        Why is he there?

02:15.436 --> 02:16.735
   If you must know, mother,

02:16.737 --> 02:18.270
     he is my doodie buddy.

02:18.272 --> 02:19.571
             Okay.

02:19.573 --> 02:21.240
   Well, I'll be right back.

02:21.242 --> 02:22.908
           (humming)
          There he is.

02:22.910 --> 02:24.910
          Whoa! Whoa!

02:24.912 --> 02:26.778
      (struggling noises)
            Oh, no.

02:26.780 --> 02:28.247
I dropped Kuchi Kopi
in the toilet

02:28.249 --> 02:29.414
and then I tried to rinse him
off in the sink

02:29.416 --> 02:30.749
and then I dropped him
in the toilet again

02:30.751 --> 02:31.750
and now there's a bunch of water

02:31.752 --> 02:33.085
   sloshing around in there.

02:33.087 --> 02:34.753
  Oh, Louise won't like that.

02:34.755 --> 02:36.421
    Yeah, Mom, that's, like,
      her favorite thing.

02:36.423 --> 02:37.923
        Don't you think
       I know that, Tina?

02:37.925 --> 02:39.424
Oh, my God, what do we do,
what do we do?

02:39.426 --> 02:40.592
              Well, we could put
                  rice around it

02:40.594 --> 02:41.593
         and put it in the oven.

02:41.595 --> 02:43.262
                            Yum.
    No, it might dry it out.

02:43.264 --> 02:44.930
   People do it with phones.
Hmm.

02:44.932 --> 02:47.166
        We should probably throw
         some ribs in there too.

02:47.168 --> 02:48.500
                   Just in case.
Mm.

02:48.502 --> 02:51.436
     Does anyone else feel
        kind of freezing

02:51.438 --> 02:52.938
       and, like, floaty?

02:52.940 --> 02:55.440
       (breathes deeply)
            Just me?

02:55.442 --> 02:57.609
      Ugh, where the hell
         is Kuchi Kopi?

02:57.611 --> 03:00.779
       (air horn blares)
Just a second.
(laughs nervously)

03:00.781 --> 03:02.447
Okay, it's at 100 degrees.

03:02.449 --> 03:04.283
So, how long does
this usually take?

03:04.285 --> 03:05.784
          30 minutes.
                     30 minutes?

03:05.786 --> 03:07.119
          That's a half an hour.

03:07.121 --> 03:08.787
                 Louise'll catch
            onto us before that.

03:08.789 --> 03:12.191
All right, look,
I know this oven pretty well.
Oven brag.

03:12.193 --> 03:14.459
So, I think if we just
turn it to 200 degrees

03:14.461 --> 03:16.662
for a few minutes,
it'll do the trick.

03:16.664 --> 03:18.130
       (air horn blares)
    Oh!

03:18.132 --> 03:19.298
I can't go in there by myself.

03:19.300 --> 03:20.799
You guys are coming with me.

03:20.801 --> 03:22.868
     What are we gonna tell her?
We just got to stall.

03:22.870 --> 03:25.037
      I could distract her
   with an intriguing dance.

03:25.039 --> 03:26.471
              Hmm?

03:26.473 --> 03:29.708
               Hey, sweetie.
         Hi.
                        Hi.
           Hey.

03:29.710 --> 03:31.977
              Hi.
    So, where's Kuchi Kopi?

03:31.979 --> 03:33.679
       Right, Kuchi Kopi.

03:33.681 --> 03:36.481
Yes.
             (Gene sings)

03:36.483 --> 03:37.816
                       Ooh!

03:37.818 --> 03:38.850
                 Look at him go.

03:38.852 --> 03:40.686
        That's so good.

03:40.688 --> 03:42.487
         Wait, Louise,
     is that your medicine?

03:42.489 --> 03:45.524
            Um, no.
            (gasps)
        You spit it out?

03:45.526 --> 03:48.560
              You're taking that
           medicine, miss missy.
         No, I am not.

03:48.562 --> 03:51.496
      Don't you make me do
   the full family hold down.

03:51.498 --> 03:53.532
       You wouldn't dare.

03:53.534 --> 03:55.367
  (all grunting and groaning)

03:55.369 --> 03:58.370
    How can she be so sick,
      but still so strong?

03:58.372 --> 03:59.738
       Like the economy!

03:59.740 --> 04:01.206
(Louise yells, then Linda yells)

04:01.208 --> 04:02.541
 Okay, that's a problem.

04:02.543 --> 04:04.843
     Oh, my God, the oven!
              ALL:
              Ah!

04:04.845 --> 04:07.045
      Oh, my God, the oven
        to you too, pal!

04:07.047 --> 04:09.214
            Oh, no,
    we left it in too long.

04:09.216 --> 04:12.050
  Maybe it'll be fine, though.

04:12.052 --> 04:14.386
                  It's not fine.
     I can fix it, I can fix it!

04:14.388 --> 04:15.687
              Ow!
           Hot Kuchi!

04:15.689 --> 04:17.555
Oh, we're dead.
We're dead.

04:17.558 --> 04:19.524
            Oh, God.
     We should just leave.

04:19.526 --> 04:20.559
             Town.

04:20.560 --> 04:22.694
Get in the car and go far away.

04:22.696 --> 04:24.062
      I'd love to see Ann Arbor.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.364
Okay, okay,

04:25.366 --> 04:27.232
uh, she's all loopy
right now, right?

04:27.234 --> 04:28.567
Maybe she won't notice?

04:28.569 --> 04:32.404
      Hi.
             Hello.
                   Hi there.

04:32.406 --> 04:34.039
(weakly):
You have... Kuchi Kopi?

04:34.041 --> 04:34.906
            Uh-huh.

04:34.908 --> 04:36.541
There he is.
Kuchi.

04:36.543 --> 04:37.876
       Okay, good night!
Good night.

04:37.878 --> 04:39.044
             Phew.

04:39.046 --> 04:41.380
       Good night, Kuchi.

04:41.382 --> 04:44.049
           (screams)
                        Oh, boy.

04:44.051 --> 04:45.717
(gibberish)
      It was an accident!

04:45.719 --> 04:47.219
  I dropped him in the toilet
       and then Tina said

04:47.221 --> 04:49.054
       we should put him
      in the oven and then

04:49.056 --> 04:51.790
Bob didn't really know the oven,
and then Gene smooshed his face,

04:51.792 --> 04:53.725
    so it's all our faults,
          right guys?

04:53.727 --> 04:54.726
                  Mm...

04:54.728 --> 04:56.395
         Louise, we're so sorry.

04:56.397 --> 04:58.730
       (angry breathing)

04:58.732 --> 05:01.566
Honey?
Say something.
            Get out.

05:01.568 --> 05:03.735
           Louise, I know you're
         really angry right now,

05:03.737 --> 05:05.404
               and it's a little
             early to, you know,

05:05.406 --> 05:07.906
        have some perspective on
     this and forgive us, but...

05:07.908 --> 05:10.142
    I will never forgive you
           for this.

05:10.144 --> 05:11.977
        Never ever ever!

05:11.979 --> 05:13.111
    How about-- what if I...

05:13.113 --> 05:14.746
            (sings)

05:14.748 --> 05:16.448
            Get out!
      Okay, okay!

