     Also, maybe if you see
the heat gun, you'll remember it

08:14.761 --> 08:16.761
  the next time I bring it up
        in conversation.

08:16.763 --> 08:19.164
  All right, we're desperate,
        so come on over.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.800
Maybe we can put the hockey game
     on in the background.
          Bye, Teddy.

08:21.802 --> 08:23.502
Teddy's coming over and
he's bringing his heat gun.

08:23.504 --> 08:25.937
      Is that a euphemism
       for his ding dong?

08:25.939 --> 08:27.939
    It's got an open floor plan,

08:27.941 --> 08:29.441
     stainless steal appliances.

08:29.443 --> 08:31.276
                     It's just a
           really great fortress

08:31.278 --> 08:33.144
                 to go to to get
               away from it all.
           (rustling)

08:33.145 --> 08:34.613
Shh.
I think I heard something.

08:34.615 --> 08:35.679
            Don't tell me shush.

08:35.682 --> 08:36.982
         (Bob's voice):
        Halt down there!

08:36.984 --> 08:39.484
     You shall not-- whoa!
              Ow!

08:39.486 --> 08:40.784
             Oh...

08:40.787 --> 08:43.154
        (clears throat)
    Uh, you shall not pass.

08:43.155 --> 08:45.290
Bakeneko?
What's going on?

08:45.292 --> 08:49.160
          Louise, I cannot allow
     you to get to the fortress.
What? Why not?

08:49.162 --> 08:51.162
(whispers): He's so jealous he's
    not invited to the fortress.

08:51.164 --> 08:52.631
                  It's pathetic.

08:52.633 --> 08:54.466
           Because the fortress
              is an awful place.

08:54.468 --> 08:56.535
            I mean, who builds a
    fortress that blocks the sun

08:56.537 --> 08:58.470
            and makes everything
                dark and gloomy?

08:58.472 --> 08:59.504
                  Who does that?

08:59.506 --> 09:01.006
           Probably a cool dude.

