10:04.538 --> 10:07.238
Oh, okay, taking a quick break.

10:07.240 --> 10:09.240
Or you can just keep walking.
That's fine.

10:09.242 --> 10:11.743
           (mumbling)
        TEDDY: Sheesh. It really
                looks messed up.

10:11.745 --> 10:13.712
You sure you don't just
want to replace it?

10:13.714 --> 10:14.946
I know a toy guy.

10:14.948 --> 10:16.715
I mean, he's real.
He's not a toy.

10:16.717 --> 10:18.383
 No, no, no, no, no, no, Teddy,
You could probably get...

10:18.385 --> 10:20.552
     she loves this thing,
      maybe more than us.

10:20.554 --> 10:22.554
   Let's just try and fix it
      before she wakes up.

10:22.556 --> 10:24.222
   Linda, you got the mustard
      for the switch out?

10:24.224 --> 10:27.225
Yes, mustard, check, right here.
         This is full.

10:27.227 --> 10:29.060
          Is this even
 the same weight as Kuchi Kopi?

10:29.062 --> 10:30.128
                  Let me see it.

10:30.130 --> 10:32.397
                 (eating sounds)
                      Now it is.

10:32.399 --> 10:33.732
         Thanks, Gene.
                 You're welcome.

10:33.734 --> 10:36.635
    (Tina groans nervously)

10:37.738 --> 10:40.238
    (all gasp, Louise stirs)

10:40.240 --> 10:41.573
      (all sigh in relief)

10:41.575 --> 10:43.475
How about putting on
that hockey game, Bobby?

10:43.477 --> 10:44.909
If we keep it low?

10:44.911 --> 10:46.911
     That was so badass, Louise.

10:46.913 --> 10:49.414
                  You were like,
          "Oh, I shall not pass?

10:49.416 --> 10:51.316
   Well, then why am I passing?"
                      (chuckles)

10:51.318 --> 10:53.418
You hear that,
everyone that may or may not

10:53.420 --> 10:55.153
be in the swamp right now?

10:55.155 --> 10:57.455
          You don't want to mess
                 with this girl.

10:57.457 --> 10:58.790
                    No sir!

10:58.792 --> 11:01.593
  (both yell, creature growls)

11:01.595 --> 11:03.094
               (nervous chuckle)
    Hello, pretty swamp monster.

11:03.096 --> 11:05.463
        You didn't hear all that
           super cool trash talk

11:05.465 --> 11:07.766
         I said before, did you?

11:07.768 --> 11:09.834
           (growling)
          (screaming):
     Okay, I guess you did!

11:14.307 --> 11:17.108
    (Akkoro Kamui growling)
   Akkoro Kamui? Is that you?

11:17.110 --> 11:18.109
       (clearing throat)
             Yeah.

11:18.111 --> 11:19.444
           (coughing)
             Yeah.

11:19.446 --> 11:20.445
        (Linda's voice):
     Uh, yes, it's me. Hi.

11:20.447 --> 11:21.446
            LOUISE:
              Hi.

11:21.448 --> 11:23.448
  So, listen, none shall pass.

11:23.450 --> 11:25.283
    Gas. (makes fart noise)
         Just kidding.

11:25.285 --> 11:28.119
But yeah, n-none shall pass. No.
       (laughs nervously)

11:28.121 --> 11:30.455
      I can't let you get
   to that fortress, Louise.

11:30.457 --> 11:32.290
     It's a bad, bad place.

11:32.292 --> 11:34.659
      Allow me to explain.
          Here we go.

11:34.661 --> 11:36.628
        ¶ That fortress
       is the worstest ¶

11:36.630 --> 11:38.296
   ¶ And it's really kind of
          cursed us ¶

11:38.298 --> 11:40.699
¶ You can see it has immersed us
       in this darkness ¶

11:40.701 --> 11:42.467
   Yup. Yeah. Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

11:42.469 --> 11:43.702
       ¶ I threw the best
        swamp parties ¶

11:43.704 --> 11:45.370
        ¶ I'd serve wine
        and calamaris ¶

11:45.372 --> 11:47.372
   ¶ And we'd drink and drink
  and drink and drink and... ¶

11:47.374 --> 11:48.807
    Yup, got it, we got it.

11:48.809 --> 11:49.974
     Hold on, I'm not done.

11:49.976 --> 11:51.476
    ¶ And we drink and drink
       and drink and... ¶

11:51.478 --> 11:53.044
      Come on, everybody!
 ¶ Drink and drink and drink ¶

11:53.046 --> 11:54.379
     ¶ And drink and drink ¶
      A little repetitive?

11:54.381 --> 11:56.314
¶ And drink and drink all day! ¶

11:56.316 --> 11:58.049
¶ But then the fortress made it
        dark and cold ¶

11:58.051 --> 12:00.318
   ¶ And that is not okay! ¶
             Yeah!

12:00.320 --> 12:02.320
Um, Kuch? Quick side bar?
Sure.

12:02.322 --> 12:03.688
         (whispering):
      What's-- what's up?

12:03.690 --> 12:05.156
         (whispering):
     Everyone's got, like,

12:05.158 --> 12:07.158
    a major problem with me
    going to this fortress.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.993
      What? No they don't.

12:08.995 --> 12:11.062
     Well, I'm just saying,
maybe there's something about it

12:11.064 --> 12:14.499
that I'm not figuring out, or...
     like it's a metaphor.

12:14.501 --> 12:16.334
     Well, maybe we get to
          the fortress

12:16.336 --> 12:18.837
    and figure it out while
  we're sitting in the Jacuzzi

12:18.839 --> 12:20.839
  with eight jet streams, hm?

12:20.841 --> 12:22.240
Yeah, okay, fine.

12:22.242 --> 12:24.242
                   (whispering):
   What are we whispering about?

12:24.244 --> 12:25.677
Oh, hey Akkoro Kamui,

12:25.679 --> 12:26.845
come here,
I want to tell you something.

12:26.847 --> 12:28.213
             Okay.

12:28.215 --> 12:29.214
         Closer.

12:29.216 --> 12:30.515
                           Okay.
          Ha!

12:30.517 --> 12:31.750
          Ow, my face!

12:33.186 --> 12:34.352
         What-- Louise?
        Where'd you go?

12:34.354 --> 12:35.754
         Whatcha doin'?

12:35.756 --> 12:37.055
           Wha? Wha?

12:37.057 --> 12:40.024
    So long, Akkoro P.U.-y!

12:40.026 --> 12:41.926
High five.
           Ah, nuts.

12:41.928 --> 12:44.028
 Hey, kind of like a ponytail.

12:44.030 --> 12:46.364
    (dryer whirring, stops)

12:46.366 --> 12:47.866
         Okay... done.

12:47.868 --> 12:50.068
           TINA: Huh.
      You gave him boobs.

12:50.070 --> 12:51.536
             Boobs?
      Those are his arms.

12:51.538 --> 12:53.037
                          Mmm...

12:53.039 --> 12:55.039
     Look, this thing works
    much better on PVC pipe.

12:55.041 --> 12:56.374
  Any chance Louise would want

12:56.376 --> 12:58.710
     two pieces of PVC pipe
        welded together?

12:58.712 --> 12:59.944
                      (sighing):
    Look, it's all right, Teddy.

12:59.946 --> 13:01.279
                    Y-You tried.

13:01.281 --> 13:03.214
Well, may I suggest
going back to the plan

13:03.216 --> 13:04.382
where you just replace it?

13:04.384 --> 13:06.050
The toy guy's over on Hillcrest.

13:06.052 --> 13:08.553
Bob, that is right by
the all-night pharmacy.

13:08.555 --> 13:09.554
And we need more medicine,

13:09.556 --> 13:10.722
since some tricky little sicky

13:10.724 --> 13:11.923
knocked it out of my hand.

13:11.925 --> 13:13.725
            Won't this toy store
                      be closed?

13:13.727 --> 13:15.894
He'll open up for an emergency.
           How do you know that?

13:15.896 --> 13:17.562
   You know when you wake up
  in the middle of the night,

13:17.564 --> 13:19.063
and all you want is to look over

13:19.065 --> 13:20.899
      and see your little
         Mumaluma doll

13:20.901 --> 13:22.901
   that you suddenly remember
      from your childhood?

13:22.903 --> 13:24.903
                 N-- uh, no.
  And you call around looking,

13:24.905 --> 13:26.571
    'cause you just want to
     pull the little string

13:26.573 --> 13:29.774
 and hear that little guy say,
     "Mumaluma, Mumaluma."

13:29.776 --> 13:31.075
                     Mm.
           No? Nobody?

13:31.077 --> 13:32.076
                     No.
          "Mumaluma."

13:32.078 --> 13:33.077
                             No.
          "Mumaluma."

13:33.079 --> 13:34.279
    No one knows "Mumaluma."

13:34.281 --> 13:35.580
                          Sorry.
Stop saying that!
           Mumaluma!

13:35.582 --> 13:36.581
          No? Nothing?
             Not ringing a bell.

13:36.583 --> 13:37.582
No.
                          Sorry.

13:37.584 --> 13:40.285
        Anyway, finally,
  an angel answers your call,

13:40.287 --> 13:43.254
  and he's willing to open up
 his shop after hours for you.

13:43.256 --> 13:44.589
      That angel is Clyde.

13:44.591 --> 13:45.924
Wait, what's the toy say again?

13:45.926 --> 13:47.425
           Mumaluma!
No no no no no!

13:47.427 --> 13:50.495
  Man, I am so sick of my toys
       trying to stop me

13:50.497 --> 13:52.263
 from going where I want to go.

13:52.265 --> 13:54.332
                  Let's face it.
               Everybody stinks.

13:54.334 --> 13:56.100
           Except me. I'm great.
                      Hey, look.

13:56.102 --> 13:57.602
We are close.
        LOUISE: Finally!

13:57.604 --> 14:00.605
 Ugh, I just want to get there,
       put up my feet...

14:00.607 --> 14:01.773
       (engines revving)
      ...and oh, come on!

14:01.775 --> 14:04.142
          (Gene's voice): Hello.
(Tina's voice): Hi.

14:04.144 --> 14:05.944
Dodomeki, Mizuchi,
don't you dare!

14:05.946 --> 14:08.446
             What?
Don't say "you shall not pass"!

14:08.448 --> 14:10.114
              Uh, well then this
                will be awkward.

14:10.116 --> 14:12.283
'Cause you
shall not pass.
                           Yeah.

14:12.285 --> 14:15.453
Listen, you're not gonna stop us
 from getting to that fortress!

14:15.455 --> 14:17.355
                 Oh, speaking of
                 the fortress...

14:17.357 --> 14:19.457
             BOTH:
        ¶ That fortress
       is the worstest ¶

14:19.459 --> 14:21.192
No no no no no no!
   ¶ And it's really kind of
          cursed us ¶

14:21.194 --> 14:23.294
No songs about
why you hate the fortress.

14:23.296 --> 14:24.963
Just really-- just really quick.
          LOUISE: No!

14:24.965 --> 14:27.966
¶ Because I like to taaaaaan-- ¶
       Stop it! Stop it!

14:27.968 --> 14:29.367
                     Mm.
He really does.

14:29.369 --> 14:31.002
Just-- let's just fight already.

14:31.004 --> 14:32.804
Okay, cool, cool, cool.

14:32.806 --> 14:34.873
Time for our game faces.
Here's mine.

14:34.875 --> 14:36.140
(growling)

14:36.142 --> 14:37.642
              Okay, here's mine.

14:37.644 --> 14:39.177
                       (howling)

14:39.179 --> 14:40.178
Wow, that's good.

14:40.180 --> 14:41.379
      Yours is really good, too.

14:41.381 --> 14:42.513
I wouldn't want to fight us.

14:42.515 --> 14:44.148
                     Me neither,
               we're terrifying.

14:44.150 --> 14:45.850
We're so ready.
Okay, Louise.

14:45.852 --> 14:47.685
       (engines revving)
         Louise?

14:47.687 --> 14:49.220
       (Louise laughing)

14:49.222 --> 14:50.321
        So long, idiots!

14:50.323 --> 14:51.389
            (grunts)

14:51.391 --> 14:52.824
            Dammit!

14:52.826 --> 14:54.025
Uh-oh.

14:54.027 --> 14:55.860
So, um, do you know
the expression,

14:55.862 --> 14:59.163
"There's an army of angry toys
heading straight for us"?

14:59.165 --> 15:00.231
                     (screaming)

15:00.233 --> 15:01.699
Okay, yup, you do.

15:01.701 --> 15:04.035
       TEDDY: <i> Uh, thanks</i>
     <i> for doing this, Clyde.</i>

15:04.037 --> 15:05.737
   Yeah, sorry to put you out
           like this.

15:05.739 --> 15:08.072
I mean, you're in your bathrobe
          and it's...

15:08.074 --> 15:09.674
         What? This is a jacket.

15:09.676 --> 15:12.043
        Oh. But... okay.

15:12.045 --> 15:14.045
                     Oh, my God,
             this is a bathrobe.

15:14.047 --> 15:15.680
  That's what I thought, yeah.

15:15.682 --> 15:17.548
          I've been wearing this
        as a jacket for a while.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.350
It looks good.
          Really good.

15:19.352 --> 15:21.185
                      (sighing):
      Let me see the Kuchi Kopi.

15:21.187 --> 15:22.186
        Let me see him.

15:22.188 --> 15:23.187
      What happened here?

15:23.189 --> 15:24.389
    Did you give him boobs?

15:24.391 --> 15:25.523
             It was an accident.

15:25.525 --> 15:27.025
Those are clearly arms, Clyde.

15:27.027 --> 15:28.726
        Look, it's my daughter's
                   favorite toy.

15:28.728 --> 15:30.728
       Please, just help us out.

15:30.730 --> 15:33.564
      (sighs) So, I assume
   you know the books, right?

15:33.566 --> 15:35.867
        What-what books?
       "What books?" Wh--

15:35.869 --> 15:37.035
               Can I talk to you
              in private, Teddy?

15:37.037 --> 15:38.536
        Sure. What's up?

15:38.538 --> 15:39.570
  What are you bringing in here?
No, he's okay.

15:39.572 --> 15:41.039
 What are you bringing in here?

15:41.041 --> 15:42.240
No, he does...
Guy doesn't even know the books!

15:42.242 --> 15:43.741
He's okay!
The books, Bobby!

15:43.743 --> 15:45.410
He's talking about the books!
You know the books.

15:45.412 --> 15:47.245
      Oh, uh, the-- what?
      Yes, the books, I--
Right?

15:47.247 --> 15:49.047
                    Right? Yeah,
           the Kuchi Kopi books.
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

15:49.049 --> 15:50.048
         You know all about 'em.
   Sit down.

15:50.050 --> 15:51.382
             What?

15:51.384 --> 15:52.717
     I'm gonna read them to you.
                       Sit down.

15:52.719 --> 15:54.385
 Oh, no, w-we don't need to...

15:54.387 --> 15:56.721
  Also, I could just read them
        at home myself.

15:56.723 --> 15:57.722
 You won't do the voices right.

15:57.724 --> 15:59.223
           Sit down.
             Okay.

15:59.225 --> 16:01.059
     All right, here we go.
          Here we go.

16:01.061 --> 16:03.594
       (creature-voice):
It all started on a chilly night

16:03.596 --> 16:05.129
     in the enchanted land of...

16:05.131 --> 16:06.264
           (knocking)
WOMAN: Clyde! Clyde!

16:06.266 --> 16:07.799
Let me in!
It's an emergency!

16:07.801 --> 16:09.067
                        Oh, boy.

16:09.069 --> 16:10.768
I need that Tanuki Baby
I called about!

16:10.770 --> 16:12.403
                      I told you
                it's not in yet!

16:12.405 --> 16:14.272
Come on, I have an apartment
full of people,

16:14.274 --> 16:15.740
        and I told them
   that I have a Tanuki Baby,

16:15.742 --> 16:16.808
      and they were like,
"No you don't." And I was like,

16:16.810 --> 16:18.242
          "Yes I do."
   And they said, "Prove it."

16:18.244 --> 16:19.911
     And I said I had to go
 to the bathroom and here I am.

16:19.913 --> 16:22.080
     I have a Tanuki Mama.
       That's all I got.

16:22.082 --> 16:23.581
I'll take it!
                Fine, all right,

16:23.583 --> 16:24.749
    I'm coming, I'm coming,
          I'm coming.

16:24.751 --> 16:26.284
  Should we... sit here, or...

16:26.286 --> 16:27.919
           You stay!
                  Yep. Got it.

16:27.921 --> 16:29.253
        (Louise panting)

16:29.255 --> 16:32.156
Bad toys! Bad toys!

16:32.158 --> 16:34.292
          KUCHI KOPI:
I know it's not the right time,
  but great drawbridge, right?

16:34.294 --> 16:36.427
Yeah yeah, very nice.
We got to close it.

16:36.429 --> 16:37.462
      We got to close it!

16:37.464 --> 16:39.430
           (grunting)

16:39.432 --> 16:40.665
        (gear cranking)

16:41.634 --> 16:42.934
            LOUISE:
              Yes!

16:42.936 --> 16:44.435
        (Louise panting)

16:44.437 --> 16:46.771
  Ha! We made it! We're safe!

16:46.773 --> 16:48.606
    Safe from all you punks!

16:48.608 --> 16:49.941
  (Linda's voice):
        Punks?
     (Tina's voice): Ouch.

16:49.943 --> 16:50.942
                 (Gene's voice):
             I think we're nice.

16:50.944 --> 16:52.110
      You know what else?

16:52.112 --> 16:54.145
 I love this friggin' fortress!

16:54.147 --> 16:56.647
  I might just sing about it!

16:56.649 --> 16:58.950
  ¶ Inside of these four walls
           of stone ¶

16:58.952 --> 17:01.619
 ¶ I'm finally all on my own ¶

17:01.621 --> 17:04.155
 ¶ 'Cause nobody's gettin' in ¶
            (grunts)

17:04.156 --> 17:06.124
 ¶ No one's on the guest list ¶

17:06.126 --> 17:08.960
       ¶ The bouncers are
         my two fists ¶

17:08.962 --> 17:11.462
¶ No one's gonna hurt this gal ¶

17:11.464 --> 17:12.964
 ¶ 'Cause nobody's gettin' in ¶

17:12.965 --> 17:14.165
         Scat break down!

17:14.166 --> 17:16.300
        ¶ Skiddy bop-ba,
        skiddy bop-ooh ¶

17:16.301 --> 17:18.368
       ¶ Skiddy bop-bop,
        bop ba-bop ooh ¶

17:18.371 --> 17:19.971
      ¶ Scatting dat dat,
        da da da dah! ¶

17:19.973 --> 17:21.638
Excuse me.
Hello.

17:21.641 --> 17:24.142
What the... Who are you?

17:24.144 --> 17:26.676
      I'm Good Kuchi Kopi.
             What?

17:26.679 --> 17:28.445
       Oh, great. The time share
        people double-booked us.

17:32.986 --> 17:34.052
            LOUISE:
   Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa...

17:34.054 --> 17:35.319
   If you're Good Kuchi Kopi,

17:35.321 --> 17:36.821
 then what does that make him?

17:36.823 --> 17:39.490
I mean, I don't really
want to say.

17:39.492 --> 17:41.325
Let's just say
I'm <i> good</i> Kuchi Kopi.

17:41.327 --> 17:43.661
   No no no no, he calls himself
                Good Kuchi Kopi.

17:43.663 --> 17:45.029
       It doesn't make him good.

17:45.031 --> 17:47.832
             I could call myself
            six-pack Kuchi Kopi,

17:47.834 --> 17:50.001
              it doesn't make me
                   have muscles!

17:50.003 --> 17:51.536
Yeah, you're looking good,
by the way.

17:51.538 --> 17:53.337
                    That is just
                so jerky of you.

17:53.339 --> 17:54.872
        You're Jerky Kuchi Kopi.

17:54.874 --> 17:56.007
You are.
                      You are!

17:56.009 --> 17:57.008
You are. You are.
                     You! You!

17:57.010 --> 17:58.009
     You are.
                   You are!

17:58.011 --> 18:00.411
What the hell is going on here?!

18:01.881 --> 18:03.047
    BOB: Wow, I had no idea
    how great Kuchi Kopi is.

18:03.049 --> 18:04.549
             TEDDY:
         He's amazing.

18:04.551 --> 18:06.350
          It's so cool how he's,
                  like, a spirit

18:06.352 --> 18:08.186
    that can be different things
            to different people.

18:08.188 --> 18:09.687
Like Tom Brady.

18:09.689 --> 18:11.856
              Clyde actually did
      a really good job reading.

18:11.858 --> 18:13.558
Yeah, he nailed
the Frog King.
                     Oh, my God,

18:13.560 --> 18:14.759
         the Frog King was good.
Yeah, right? Huh?

18:14.761 --> 18:16.027
That's very good.

18:16.029 --> 18:17.728
       Okay, so, what are
        you doing here,

18:17.730 --> 18:19.897
       "Good Kuchi Kopi"?

18:19.899 --> 18:21.732
       Besides killing the vibe.

18:21.734 --> 18:24.102
You don't get it yet,
do you Louise?

18:24.104 --> 18:25.770
What this place is?

18:25.772 --> 18:28.539
Why we've all been trying
to stop you from getting here?

18:28.541 --> 18:30.708
          No, I don't.
      But you can keep on

18:30.710 --> 18:32.610
   being mysterious about it,
          if you want.

18:32.612 --> 18:35.580
Closing yourself off
like this, Louise?

18:35.582 --> 18:39.750
Hm? Building angry walls
around yourself, Louise?

18:39.752 --> 18:41.719
You need to forgive
your family.

18:41.721 --> 18:44.388
   What? Oh, that's what this
         is all about?

18:44.390 --> 18:46.057
Well, the answer is no!

18:46.059 --> 18:47.892
Okay? I mean,
look what they did.

18:47.894 --> 18:49.727
Look at his face. He's hideous.

18:49.729 --> 18:51.395
  Okay, that's not necessary.

18:51.397 --> 18:54.899
 Forgiving your family would be
     good for you, Louise.

18:54.901 --> 18:56.734
 Mm-mm. Mm-mm. Not gonna do it.

18:56.736 --> 19:00.404
       ¶ You think living
      behind these walls ¶

19:00.406 --> 19:01.906
                        Stop it.
      No, I won't stop it.

19:01.908 --> 19:03.908
            The end. Great song.
     No, it's not the end.

19:03.910 --> 19:06.744
   ¶ Means you can't get hurt
            at all ¶

19:06.746 --> 19:07.745
                        (scoffs)
                       This guy.

19:07.747 --> 19:08.746
                Huh, am I right?

19:08.748 --> 19:10.148
        Shush. Be quiet.

19:10.150 --> 19:13.751
    ¶ But that just makes it
         dark outside ¶

19:13.753 --> 19:16.654
